PROWL just gestured at the screen. &quot;I don&#39;t know much about the Matrix
itself.&quot; he said carefully, almost reverantly. &quot;But I know that from
its history it decides who is worthy and who is not. I don&#39;t know why
it chooses the way it chooses.&quot;

&quot;There is some good news then.&quot; LORD ELDER said over the comlink. &quot;The
energy field is unstable right now. It must be taking a lot of energy
to feed that.&quot; He grunted slightly. &quot;They must be feeding off a live
Autobot with the Matrix still in their chest.&quot;

PROWL nodded, &quot;So if it is Rodimus they are getting this from he must
still be alive!&quot;

&quot;Yes.&quot; LORD ELDER said. &quot;However there is also a danger.&quot;

ELDER paused as if to highlight the gravity of his next point. &quot;The
only way we have to defend ourselves against Unicron is the Matrix. If
a way can be found to intergrate the Matrix energy with Unicron&#39;s,
then Unicron may no longer be as vulnerable to the energies of the
Matrix.&quot;

PROWL gaped, his jaw dropping, &quot;Whoever is doing this is playing a
dangerous game.&quot;

&quot;A game that must be stopped.&quot; LORD ELDER said. &quot;Before it is too late.&quot;

